            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1897.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong>,<strong> </strong>then slice your<strong> portobello mushroom[s]</strong> into wedges and add to the tray</p><p>Sprinkle over the<strong> remaining</strong> <strong>thyme leaves</strong>, drizzle with<strong> olive oil</strong> and season generously with<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 5-6 min or until the portobello wedges are cooked through – these are your<strong> thyme-roasted portobellos</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1897.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
